151:     // The response code for an individual descriptor.
152:     Code code = 1;
153: 
154:     // The current limit as configured by the server. Useful for debugging, etc.
155:     RateLimit current_limit = 2;
156: 
157:     // The limit remaining in the current time unit.
158:     uint32 limit_remaining = 3;
159: 
160:     // Duration until reset of the current limit window.
161:     google.protobuf.Duration duration_until_reset = 4;
162: 
163:     // Quota is available for a request if its descriptor set has cached quota available for all
164:     // descriptors.
165:     // This is for each individual descriptor in the descriptor set. The client will perform matches for each individual descriptor against available per-descriptor quota.
166:     //
167:     // If quota is available, a RLS request will not be made and the quota will be reduced by 1 for
168:     // all matching descriptors.
169:     //
170:     // If there is not sufficient quota, there are three cases:
171:     // 1. A cached entry exists for a RLS descriptor that is out-of-quota, but not expired.
172:     //    In this case, the request will be treated as OVER_LIMIT.
173:     // 2. Some RLS descriptors have a cached entry that has valid quota but some RLS descriptors
174:     //    have no cached entry. This will trigger a new RLS request.
175:     //    When the result is returned, a single unit will be consumed from the quota for all
176:     //    matching descriptors.
177:     //    If the server did not provide a quota, such as the quota message is empty for some of
178:     //    the descriptors, then the request admission is determined by the
179:     //    :ref:`overall_code <envoy_v3_api_field_service.ratelimit.v3.RateLimitResponse.overall_code>`.
180:     // 3. All RLS descriptors lack a cached entry, this will trigger a new RLS request,
181:     //    When the result is returned, a single unit will be consumed from the quota for all
